WHO   — THE SPONGE — a life-science sphere — the brainless mind
WHAT  — An animal with no neurons, no muscles, no organs, no symmetry — just a colony of cells pumping water through a living filter. Yet it contracts, 'sneezes' to clear its pores, and, if pushed through a sieve into single cells, will crawl back together and rebuild itself. The other floor of animal life, beside Trichoplax.
